The free app only let me use 1 playlist so I made the leap and purchased the pro version.  I had over 4000 songs so it took all night to move everything but it's done.  The other reviews say that it won't put your music on an SD card but I was able to.  I was also able to bring over my entire music collection.  1 of the playlist is titled "music".  However, there is also a playlist entitled "library" which I had to uncheck.  Library was everything in my itunes, movies and TV shows, etc, etc.  So be careful with that list.    The instructions were easy to follow and other than taking all night, it was a breeze to get everything over.  Great job guys!!!

Not a big deal though, the extension doesn't interfere with ordering or searching.

content: It probably works fine if you only have a few songs to sync, but I have over 30 Gigs of music, so it takes a long time. This, by itself, isn't a problem. The trouble is that if I add a single playlist, with, say only 20 songs, it still takes hours to sync. It seems to be copying songs that have already been synced (which is a lot of songs). It knows to skip some of them, but it needs to skip a lot more.  On top of that, the Mac interface is a bit clunky. I can see all the playlists that I've asked it to sync, but they're in the order that I added them, rather than alphabetical order, which would make it easier to find them. So it makes managing my playlists a lot more work than it should be.  That said, it gets the job done.

I have two Samsung phones-- an S2 Skyrocket and an S3. After trying to figure out the best way to transfer the music that I have in iTunes as well as other music on my computer.... I came across this app. It installed easily on my phone and Win8 Pro PC and once I tried the free version and saw how easy it worked, I immediately purchased the paid pro version without hesitation. Once I did that, I was able to transfer over 500 songs that I wanted to without having to touch a single cable.  After the one phone, I then went to do the other.... and ran into a problem. I saw that people had emailed them, and received a response quickly.... so at 11pm EST I did just that.... and within minutes I received a response that contained a simple solution that worked. All I had to do was uncheck everything, sync, and then check what I wanted to sync and presto it all worked on the second phone without a problem.  A definite simple and elegant solution for transferring iTunes to my phones.
